Keep format style:
1. block should not start with a whitespace (wsl)
2. comment should end in a period (godot)
3. return statements should not be cuddled if block has more than two lines (wsl)
4. assignments should only be cuddled with other assignments (wsl)
5. unexported-return: exported func smth returns unexported type smth, which can be annoying to use (revive)
6. revive: enforce-switch-style: switch must have a default case clause
7. noinlineerr: avoid inline error handling using `if err := ...; err != nil`; use plain assignment `err := ...`
8. embeddedstructfieldcheck: there must be an empty line separating embedded fields from regular fields
9. do not use tc := tc local variable in tests
10. use below golang package imports formatting structure:
<standard packages>
<empty line>
<external packages>
<empty line>
<external gitlab or github packages>
<empty line>
<current project packages>
ex.
import (
    "fmt"

    "github.com/google/uuid"

    "gitlab.com/abc/utils"

    "threat/internal/model"
) 
11. if it's a test function use below rules:
do not use helper function
all test should use test suite or table tests like
tests := []struct{
    name string
    // fields

    expected SomeExpected
    err      error
}{
    {
        name: ""
    }
}
or test suite that uses mockery 